## Fix R2RML import URI mismatch (hash vs slash) so mappings apply

Context: After importing an R2RML mapping file, the import reported success
and persisted the mappings, but they showed as "Not Mapped" in the Mapping
Designer / Manual page and the knowledge graph could not be built. Root cause:
ontology entity/property URIs are hash-terminated (e.g.
`https://example.com/MyOntology#Capacity`) while imported R2RML class/predicate
URIs are slash-separated (`.../Capacity`), and every designer join uses exact
string equality. Diagnostics and re-export worked because they iterate the
stored assignment directly. Fix normalizes imported URIs to the ontology's
canonical URIs at import time, by local name (exact-case then case-insensitive),
so all downstream consumers (designer, diagnostics, export, KG build) agree.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/mapping/Mapping.py
   Added `_canonicalize_imported_uris` (static) and called it from
   `parse_r2rml` to rewrite imported `ontology_class` / `property` URIs to the
   loaded ontology's canonical URIs via local-name lookup; unmatched URIs and
   the no-ontology case are left untouched.
2. tests/units/mapping/test_mapping_service.py
   Added `TestParseR2rmlUriNormalization` covering slash→hash rewrite for
   entity class and relationship property URIs, unmatched-URI passthrough, and
   the empty-ontology no-op.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/mapping/Mapping.py
- tests/units/mapping/test_mapping_service.py

