## Add build-run tracing (analytics) to the registry

Context: Builds (Digital Twin triple-store materializations) left no durable
trace — manual/API builds only existed as in-memory TaskManager tasks, and the
scheduler kept a thin, capped `schedule_runs` history with limited stats. There
was no way to analyse build history (durations, counts, success rate) per
domain/version after the fact. This adds a new append-only `build_runs` table in
the Lakebase registry that records one immutable row per build across every path
(UI session, external API, scheduler), linked to the `domains` row and keyed by
the tuple `(domain_id, version)`. Many rows per tuple are expected; the "active"
build for a `(domain, version)` is derived as the most recent successful run by
`started_at` (no flag). The table self-heals on upgraded deployments via a lazy
`CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` guard, so no manual re-Initialize is needed. A read
API and a registry "Build Analytics" panel surface the history and aggregates.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/schema.sql
   Added the `build_runs` table (FK `domain_id -> domains(id)` ON DELETE CASCADE,
   version + build_kind + status + timings + counts + engine/sync + jsonb
   phase_times/stats) and `idx_build_runs_domain_version` index.
2. src/back/objects/registry/store/base.py
   Added `BuildRunEntry` TypedDict and three abstract methods —
   `record_build_run`, `load_build_runs`, `build_analytics`.
3. src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py
   Implemented the three methods with psycopg3 plus a guarded
   `_ensure_build_runs_table()` (lazy idempotent CREATE for old deployments);
   registered `build_runs` in `_KNOWN_TABLES` and the module docstring.
4. src/back/objects/registry/RegistryService.py
   Added thin facade wrappers `record_build_run` / `load_build_runs` /
   `build_analytics` delegating to the store (best-effort on write).
5. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py
   Record a build-run trace exactly once per build via a `_record_build_run`
   helper wired into `_complete_task` (success), the empty-view early-complete,
   `_fail_unexpected` (error), the cancel path, and a `finally` guard for
   phase-level failures; resolve folder/version/engine/counts from pipeline state.
6. src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py
   Record a `scheduled` build-run in `_run_scheduled_build`'s finally block
   (independent of the legacy `schedule_runs` write).
7. src/back/objects/domain/SettingsService.py
   Added `get_build_runs_result` and `get_build_analytics_result`.
8. src/api/routers/internal/settings.py
   Added `GET /settings/build-runs/{domain}` and
   `GET /settings/build-analytics/{domain}` (optional `version`, `limit`).
9. src/front/config/menu_config.json
   Added a "Build Analytics" item to the registry Automation group.
10. src/front/templates/partials/registry/_registry_build_analytics.html,
    src/front/static/config/js/build-analytics.js,
    src/front/templates/registry.html
    New panel (domain + version selectors, summary cards, runs table with the
    active build highlighted) and its wiring/script include.
11. tests/units/registry/test_registry_store.py
    Implemented the new methods on the in-memory fake and added contract tests
    for round-trip ordering, version filtering, analytics aggregation, and the
    empty-domain case.

